<ns1228:article xmlns:ns1228="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.development.eskom.tokenVending.referenceImplementation.proposal.proposal">

  <ns1229:articleinfo xmlns:ns1229="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1230:title xmlns:ns1230="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Architectural assessment process </ns1230:title>
    <ns1231:date xmlns:ns1231="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">31 May 2004</ns1231:date>
    
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" href="../../../../../../resources/information/solms/resources/skills/authors/fritzSolmsContact.docbook"/>
    
  </ns1229:articleinfo>
  
  <ns1232:section xmlns:ns1232="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1233:title xmlns:ns1233="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Overview</ns1233:title>
    <ns1234:para xmlns:ns1234="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The architectural assessment process aims to assess an architecture from a business
      objectives perspective. The process steps are
      <ns1235:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1235="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1236:listitem xmlns:ns1236="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1237:para xmlns:ns1237="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Elicitation</ns1237:para></ns1236:listitem>
        <ns1238:listitem xmlns:ns1238="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1239:para xmlns:ns1239="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Analysis</ns1239:para></ns1238:listitem>
        <ns1240:listitem xmlns:ns1240="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1241:para xmlns:ns1241="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Architectural optimization</ns1241:para></ns1240:listitem>
        <ns1242:listitem xmlns:ns1242="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1243:para xmlns:ns1243="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Validation and estimation</ns1243:para></ns1242:listitem>
      </ns1235:itemizedlist>
    </ns1234:para>
  </ns1232:section>
  

 
<ns1244:section xmlns:ns1244="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.evaluating.solms.methodology">

  <ns1245:title xmlns:ns1245="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Elicitation</ns1245:title>
  <ns1246:para xmlns:ns1246="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
     During this phase the business vision, goals, the desired quality attributes and the
     chosen architecture are communicated.
    The core steps during the elicitation phase are
    <ns1247:orderedlist xmlns:ns1247="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns1248:listitem xmlns:ns1248="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1249:para xmlns:ns1249="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Define the team.</ns1249:para></ns1248:listitem>
      <ns1250:listitem xmlns:ns1250="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1251:para xmlns:ns1251="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Identify the business drivers.</ns1251:para></ns1250:listitem>
      <ns1252:listitem xmlns:ns1252="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1253:para xmlns:ns1253="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Understand the proposed/implemented architecture.</ns1253:para></ns1252:listitem>
      <ns1254:listitem xmlns:ns1254="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1255:para xmlns:ns1255="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Understand architectural approaches.</ns1255:para></ns1254:listitem>
    </ns1247:orderedlist>  
  </ns1246:para>
  
  <ns1256:section xmlns:ns1256="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1257:title xmlns:ns1257="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Define the team</ns1257:title>
    <ns1258:para xmlns:ns1258="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      In this phase we identify the persons who will be involved in the architectural assessment
      and the roles they play in the process.
      The team should include
      <ns1259:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1259="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1260:listitem xmlns:ns1260="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1261:formalpara xmlns:ns1261="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1262:title xmlns:ns1262="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Business</ns1262:title>
          <ns1263:para xmlns:ns1263="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            The business representative(s) should be able to provide
            <ns1264:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1264="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              <ns1265:listitem xmlns:ns1265="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1266:para xmlns:ns1266="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                the vision business has for system/project,
              </ns1266:para></ns1265:listitem>
              <ns1267:listitem xmlns:ns1267="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1268:para xmlns:ns1268="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                the business drivers for the project/system, and 
              </ns1268:para></ns1267:listitem>
              <ns1269:listitem xmlns:ns1269="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1270:para xmlns:ns1270="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                if the system is already in use, 
                any issues business has with the system.  
              </ns1270:para></ns1269:listitem>
            </ns1264:itemizedlist>
          </ns1263:para>
        </ns1261:formalpara></ns1260:listitem>
        <ns1271:listitem xmlns:ns1271="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1272:formalpara xmlns:ns1272="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1273:title xmlns:ns1273="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Business analysis</ns1273:title>
          <ns1274:para xmlns:ns1274="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            The business analyst(s) should be able to elaborate around the business vision and drivers. 
            Additionally business analysis should be able to
            <ns1275:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1275="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              <ns1276:listitem xmlns:ns1276="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1277:para xmlns:ns1277="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                define the users and secondary actors of the system,   
              </ns1277:para></ns1276:listitem>
              <ns1278:listitem xmlns:ns1278="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1279:para xmlns:ns1279="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                define the scope of the project/system (the abstract, high-level use cases), 
              </ns1279:para></ns1278:listitem>
              <ns1280:listitem xmlns:ns1280="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1281:para xmlns:ns1281="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                define the non-functional requirements (quality attributes like performance, 
                scaleability, availability, reliability, usability, modifiability, integrability, ...)
              </ns1281:para></ns1280:listitem>
              <ns1282:listitem xmlns:ns1282="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1283:para xmlns:ns1283="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                provide details about the functional requirements when required, and
              </ns1283:para></ns1282:listitem>
              <ns1284:listitem xmlns:ns1284="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1285:para xmlns:ns1285="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                if the system is in use already,  any issues experienced by users and the business
                with the system.
              </ns1285:para></ns1284:listitem>
              <ns1286:note xmlns:ns1286="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1287:para xmlns:ns1287="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                Should the organization not have formal business analysts, this information should
                be provided by those who are involved in the requirements for the system/project.
              </ns1287:para></ns1286:note>
            </ns1275:itemizedlist>  
          </ns1274:para>
        </ns1272:formalpara></ns1271:listitem>
        <ns1288:listitem xmlns:ns1288="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1289:formalpara xmlns:ns1289="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1290:title xmlns:ns1290="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Architecture</ns1290:title>
          <ns1291:para xmlns:ns1291="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            Architecture should be able to provide information on the following:
            <ns1292:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1292="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              <ns1293:listitem xmlns:ns1293="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1294:para xmlns:ns1294="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                  The drivers on which the architectural decisions made were based.
                </ns1294:para></ns1293:listitem>
              <ns1295:listitem xmlns:ns1295="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1296:para xmlns:ns1296="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                  The architectural trade-offs made in the process of designing the architecture.
                </ns1296:para></ns1295:listitem>
              <ns1297:listitem xmlns:ns1297="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1298:para xmlns:ns1298="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                  The architecture for the system/project.
                </ns1298:para></ns1297:listitem>
                <ns1299:listitem xmlns:ns1299="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1300:para xmlns:ns1300="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                  Any issues architecture is aware of.
                </ns1300:para></ns1299:listitem>
            </ns1292:itemizedlist>
            <ns1301:note xmlns:ns1301="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1302:para xmlns:ns1302="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              A lot of this information can be reverse engineered, should architecture not 
              be able to provide the information.
            </ns1302:para></ns1301:note>
          </ns1291:para>
        </ns1289:formalpara></ns1288:listitem>
        <ns1303:listitem xmlns:ns1303="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1304:formalpara xmlns:ns1304="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1305:title xmlns:ns1305="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Design/development team</ns1305:title>
          <ns1306:para xmlns:ns1306="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            The designer/developers should be able to specify
            <ns1307:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1307="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              <ns1308:listitem xmlns:ns1308="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1309:para xmlns:ns1309="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                 how efficient they are able to design/develop within the architecture, and
              </ns1309:para></ns1308:listitem>
              <ns1310:listitem xmlns:ns1310="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1311:para xmlns:ns1311="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                 any difficulties they experience in realizing requirements within the architecture.
              </ns1311:para></ns1310:listitem>
            </ns1307:itemizedlist>
          </ns1306:para>
        </ns1304:formalpara></ns1303:listitem>
      </ns1259:itemizedlist>
    </ns1258:para>
  </ns1256:section>
  
  <ns1312:section xmlns:ns1312="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1313:title xmlns:ns1313="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Identify the business drivers</ns1313:title>
    <ns1314:para xmlns:ns1314="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The starting point is typically the <ns1315:emphasis xmlns:ns1315="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">vision and scope document</ns1315:emphasis>    
      which includes
      <ns1316:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1316="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1317:listitem xmlns:ns1317="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1318:para xmlns:ns1318="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the vision the organization is trying to realize with the project,</ns1318:para></ns1317:listitem>
        <ns1319:listitem xmlns:ns1319="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1320:para xmlns:ns1320="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the business objectives,</ns1320:para></ns1319:listitem>
        <ns1321:listitem xmlns:ns1321="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1322:para xmlns:ns1322="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core stake holders of the system/project</ns1322:para></ns1321:listitem>
        <ns1323:listitem xmlns:ns1323="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1324:para xmlns:ns1324="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the financial context including a return on investment estimation,</ns1324:para></ns1323:listitem>
        <ns1325:listitem xmlns:ns1325="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1326:para xmlns:ns1326="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core use cases (functional requirements) of the system,</ns1326:para></ns1325:listitem>
        <ns1327:listitem xmlns:ns1327="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1328:para xmlns:ns1328="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core limitations (exclusions),</ns1328:para></ns1327:listitem>
        <ns1329:listitem xmlns:ns1329="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1330:para xmlns:ns1330="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core quality attributes,</ns1330:para></ns1329:listitem>
        <ns1331:listitem xmlns:ns1331="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1332:para xmlns:ns1332="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any constraints placed on the project or the architecture, and</ns1332:para></ns1331:listitem>
        <ns1333:listitem xmlns:ns1333="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1334:para xmlns:ns1334="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any dependencies the project may have.</ns1334:para></ns1333:listitem>
      </ns1316:itemizedlist>
    </ns1314:para>
  </ns1312:section>
  
  <ns1335:section xmlns:ns1335="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1336:title xmlns:ns1336="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Understand the proposed/implemented architecture</ns1336:title>
    <ns1337:para xmlns:ns1337="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       The lead architect provides the essence of the architecture in a concise, structured way.
       The presentation is expected to have <ns1338:quote xmlns:ns1338="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1339:emphasis xmlns:ns1339="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">a low signal to noise ratio</ns1339:emphasis></ns1338:quote>
       in the sense that it should focus on the architectural core and not stray into auxiliary details.
       The presentation should cover
       <ns1340:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1340="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns1341:listitem xmlns:ns1341="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1342:para xmlns:ns1342="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the context of the architecture which covers the environment in which the system
           will live/ is living,
         </ns1342:para></ns1341:listitem>
         <ns1343:listitem xmlns:ns1343="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1344:para xmlns:ns1344="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the technical constraints (<ns1345:abbrev xmlns:ns1345="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">e.g.</ns1345:abbrev> the required deployment platforms and
           middle ware technologies),
         </ns1344:para></ns1343:listitem>
         <ns1346:listitem xmlns:ns1346="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1347:para xmlns:ns1347="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the architectural approaches including
           <ns1348:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1348="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
             <ns1349:listitem xmlns:ns1349="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1350:para xmlns:ns1350="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any reference architecture employed,</ns1350:para></ns1349:listitem>
             <ns1351:listitem xmlns:ns1351="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1352:para xmlns:ns1352="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the architectural patterns which were enlisted,</ns1352:para></ns1351:listitem>
             <ns1353:listitem xmlns:ns1353="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1354:para xmlns:ns1354="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the tactics which were realized.</ns1354:para></ns1353:listitem>
           </ns1348:itemizedlist>
         </ns1347:para></ns1346:listitem>
       </ns1340:itemizedlist>
       <ns1355:note xmlns:ns1355="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1356:para xmlns:ns1356="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         A lot of the above information can be reverse engineered by the architectural assessment team.  
       </ns1356:para></ns1355:note>
    </ns1337:para>
  </ns1335:section>
  
  <ns1357:section xmlns:ns1357="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1358:title xmlns:ns1358="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Understand architectural approaches</ns1358:title>
    <ns1359:para xmlns:ns1359="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       This step a discussion with the lead architect and the architecture team in order to
       <ns1360:emphasis xmlns:ns1360="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">verify and deepen and broaden the architectural understanding</ns1360:emphasis>.
       Usually the use further architectural patterns is identified.
    </ns1359:para>
  </ns1357:section>
</ns1244:section>  
  
<ns1361:section xmlns:ns1361="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <ns1362:title xmlns:ns1362="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Analysis</ns1362:title>
  <ns1363:para xmlns:ns1363="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    During the analysis phase an in-depth analysis of the existing architecture, any potential issues
    and possible modifications
  </ns1363:para>

  <ns1364:section xmlns:ns1364="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1365:title xmlns:ns1365="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Generate a quality attribute utility tree</ns1365:title>
    <ns1366:para xmlns:ns1366="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      In this step, taken from ATAM, the <ns1367:emphasis xmlns:ns1367="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Architectural Trade-Off Analysis Method</ns1367:emphasis>,
      the architectural assessment team generates
      <ns1368:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1368="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1369:listitem xmlns:ns1369="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1370:para xmlns:ns1370="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a utility tree containing the quality attributes and the scenarios they affect, and
        </ns1370:para></ns1369:listitem>
        <ns1371:listitem xmlns:ns1371="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1372:para xmlns:ns1372="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a prioritized list of scenarios extracted from the utility tree.  
        </ns1372:para></ns1371:listitem>
      </ns1368:itemizedlist>
    </ns1366:para>
    
    <ns1373:section xmlns:ns1373="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns1374:title xmlns:ns1374="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Utility trees</ns1374:title>
      <ns1375:para xmlns:ns1375="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        Utility trees show how the required quality attributes are supported by the architecture and how
        the resultant architecture realizes these quality attributes. They have 
        <ns1376:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1376="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1377:listitem xmlns:ns1377="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1378:para xmlns:ns1378="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            a quality attribute at their root,    
          </ns1378:para></ns1377:listitem>
          <ns1379:listitem xmlns:ns1379="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1380:para xmlns:ns1380="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            refined attributes in the next layer of the tree, and  
          </ns1380:para></ns1379:listitem>
          <ns1381:listitem xmlns:ns1381="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1382:para xmlns:ns1382="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            scenarios which have a dependency on that quality attribute in the third layer.  
          </ns1382:para></ns1381:listitem>
        </ns1376:itemizedlist>
      </ns1375:para>
    </ns1373:section>
    
  </ns1364:section>
  
  <ns1383:section xmlns:ns1383="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1384:title xmlns:ns1384="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Analyze architectural approaches</ns1384:title>
    <ns1385:para xmlns:ns1385="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The scenarios are analyzed one by one in priority order:
      <ns1386:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1386="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1387:listitem xmlns:ns1387="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1388:para xmlns:ns1388="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The architect is asked to explain how the architecture supports each scenario.  
          <ns1389:note xmlns:ns1389="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1390:para xmlns:ns1390="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
             The architectural assessment team can reverse engineer this information if necessary. 
          </ns1390:para></ns1389:note>
        </ns1388:para></ns1387:listitem>
        <ns1391:listitem xmlns:ns1391="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1392:para xmlns:ns1392="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The architectural assessment team identifies and documents the architectural decisions with their
          risks, non-risks, sensitivity points and trade offs.  
        </ns1392:para></ns1391:listitem>
      </ns1386:itemizedlist>
    </ns1385:para>
  </ns1383:section>
  
  <ns1393:section xmlns:ns1393="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1394:title xmlns:ns1394="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Document the architecture if sufficient documentation does not exist</ns1394:title>
    <ns1395:para xmlns:ns1395="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The architecture, the trade-off decisions as well as the rationale behind these
      will be documented, where relevant using UML.
    </ns1395:para>
  </ns1393:section>
</ns1361:section>

<ns1396:section xmlns:ns1396="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <ns1397:title xmlns:ns1397="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Architectural Optimization</ns1397:title>
  <ns1398:para xmlns:ns1398="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    In this phase the architectural assessment team will explore ways in which the architecture 
    can be improved.  
  </ns1398:para>
  <ns1399:section xmlns:ns1399="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1400:title xmlns:ns1400="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Identify and document suggested modifications to the architecture</ns1400:title>
    <ns1401:para xmlns:ns1401="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      At this stage the architectural assessment team looks at quality attributes required
      by the business which are net effectively realized by the existing architecture and
      any other issues identified in the current architecture and explores ways in which
      the current architecture can be improved.
    </ns1401:para>
    <ns1402:para xmlns:ns1402="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The proposed architectural changes will be documented, using UML where applicable.
      The impact of  the architectural modifications will be analyzed and documented.
    </ns1402:para>
  </ns1399:section>
</ns1396:section>

<ns1403:section xmlns:ns1403="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <ns1404:title xmlns:ns1404="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Validation and estimation</ns1404:title>
  <ns1405:para xmlns:ns1405="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    During this phase the impact of any changes to the architecture will be validated 
    against the business objectives and a cost/benefit analysis will be performed.
  </ns1405:para>
  
  <ns1406:section xmlns:ns1406="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1407:title xmlns:ns1407="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Cost estimate of the proposed architectural modifications</ns1407:title>
    <ns1408:para xmlns:ns1408="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      At this stage the architectural assessment team together with development will 
      assess the cost implications of the proposed changes to the architecture.
    </ns1408:para>
  </ns1406:section>
  
  
  <ns1409:section xmlns:ns1409="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1410:title xmlns:ns1410="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Validate suggested modifications with the business</ns1410:title>
    <ns1411:para xmlns:ns1411="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The impact of the suggested architectural modifications in terms of impact on the
      business objectives and quality attributes as well as the cost impact
      will be discussed with business. The benefit too the business will be assessed
      at this stage.
    </ns1411:para>
  </ns1409:section>
  
  <ns1412:section xmlns:ns1412="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1413:title xmlns:ns1413="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Assess the cost/benefit of the proposed architectural modifications</ns1413:title>
    <ns1414:para xmlns:ns1414="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The architectural assessment team will finally document the cost/benefit of any
      proposed architectural changes.
    </ns1414:para>
  </ns1412:section>
  
</ns1403:section>


  <ns1415:section xmlns:ns1415="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1416:title xmlns:ns1416="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Deliverables</ns1416:title>
    <ns1417:para xmlns:ns1417="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The deliverables of the architectural assessment include
      <ns1418:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1418="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1419:listitem xmlns:ns1419="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1420:para xmlns:ns1420="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a summary of the business context,  
        </ns1420:para></ns1419:listitem>
        <ns1421:listitem xmlns:ns1421="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1422:para xmlns:ns1422="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a list of the architectural drivers including the quality attribute weightings,  
        </ns1422:para></ns1421:listitem>
        <ns1423:listitem xmlns:ns1423="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1424:para xmlns:ns1424="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a list of the architectural trade-offs made and an analysis of the validity,  
        </ns1424:para></ns1423:listitem>
        <ns1425:listitem xmlns:ns1425="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1426:para xmlns:ns1426="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          an architectural design document if the architecture was not sufficiently documented prior to the assessment,  
        </ns1426:para></ns1425:listitem>
        <ns1427:listitem xmlns:ns1427="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1428:para xmlns:ns1428="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          if applicable, a list of improvements which can be made to the architecture including
          <ns1429:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1429="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            <ns1430:listitem xmlns:ns1430="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1431:para xmlns:ns1431="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              the issue(s) addressed by the proposed improvements, 
            </ns1431:para></ns1430:listitem>
            <ns1432:listitem xmlns:ns1432="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1433:para xmlns:ns1433="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              the actual proposed modifications to the architecture,  
            </ns1433:para></ns1432:listitem>
            <ns1434:listitem xmlns:ns1434="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1435:para xmlns:ns1435="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              an impact analysis on the quality attributes of the system.  
            </ns1435:para></ns1434:listitem>
            <ns1436:listitem xmlns:ns1436="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1437:para xmlns:ns1437="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              the benefits of the changes to the business, and
            </ns1437:para></ns1436:listitem>
            <ns1438:listitem xmlns:ns1438="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1439:para xmlns:ns1439="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              a cost/benefit analysis of the proposed changes.  
            </ns1439:para></ns1438:listitem>
          </ns1429:itemizedlist>
        </ns1428:para></ns1427:listitem>
      </ns1418:itemizedlist>
      
    </ns1417:para>
  </ns1415:section>
</ns1228:article>